# CODEOWNERS — protected paths require the owner's review (CONTRACT §8/§10).
#
# These are the same "an autonomous engine may NEVER touch this without review"
# paths the policy gate (scripts/policy-gate.mjs / lib/policy.ts) classifies as
# Tier C. CODEOWNERS makes GitHub *request* @ShravG1's review on any PR touching
# them; with branch protection requiring code-owner review, that review becomes
# mandatory. The CI policy-gate is the belt to this braces: it goes red on an
# engine-authored PR that touches these, so the autonomous merger can't slip one
# through even before branch protection is on.
#
# Everything else has no owner here on purpose — only the protected set needs the
# gate. Order matters: later patterns win, so the catch-all is first.

# (no default owner — unprotected paths don't force review)

# Secrets / environment
.env*                       @ShravG1
**/.env*                    @ShravG1

# CI / automation / this file itself
/.github/                   @ShravG1
/CODEOWNERS                 @ShravG1

# Auth, middleware, request edge
/lib/auth.ts                @ShravG1
/middleware.*               @ShravG1
/lib/mutations.ts           @ShravG1

# Deploy / build config
/vercel.json                @ShravG1
/vercel.ts                  @ShravG1
/next.config.*              @ShravG1

# Database schema / migrations
**/migrations/**            @ShravG1
*.sql                       @ShravG1

# The policy manifest and the contract themselves
*.policy.json               @ShravG1
/CONTRACT.md                @ShravG1
